library(shiny)
data <- readMat("data/referencedatabasebiomolecules.mat")
# Extract X-axis data
x <- data$Xaxis

# Loop through each sample and plot against X-axis
for (i in 1:60) {
  # Extract y-axis data for current sample
  y <- data[[i]]

  # Plot current sample against X-axis
  plot(x, y, type = "l", main = names(data)[i])
}

# Define the user interface (UI)
ui <- fluidPage(
  checkboxGroupInput("samples", "Select samples to plot:", choices = names(data), selected = c(names(data)[1])),
  plotOutput("plot")
)

# Define the server logic
server <- function(input, output) {
  output$plot <- renderPlot({
    # Extract X-axis data
    x <- data$Xaxis

    # Plot the selected samples
    if (length(input$samples) > 0) {
      plot(x, data[[input$samples[1]]], type = "l", main = input$samples[1], ylim = range(unlist(data[input$samples])))

      for (i in 2:length(input$samples)) {
        lines(x, data[[input$samples[i]]], col = rainbow(length(input$samples))[i])
      }

      # Add a legend
      legend("topright", legend = input$samples, col = rainbow(length(input$samples)), lty = 1)
    } else {
      # Display a message if no samples are selected
      message("No samples selected.")
    }
  })
}

# Run the application
shinyApp(ui, server)
